2) Autherization : Roles
=========================

   1) Role:  its set of instructions which allow commands for any user.
   	Types of roles:
   		1. default role : 
   		2. custom role :
   	
   	Scope:
   	1. cluster scope:
   	2. namespace scope:
   	
   	pv : cluster
   	pvc : namespace
   	pod : namespace
   	
   	kubectl api-resource <== to check scope.
   	
   	
   	Types of role scope in k8s.
   	1) Cluster scope.
   	2) Namespace scope.
   	
   2. Rolebinding : when we delegate role to user/group it call rolebinding.
   
	Types.
	1. Cluster level.
		Note: Cluster level rolebinding must have cluster scope level.
		
	2. Namespace level.
		Note: role might have cluster/namespace scope for Namespace level rolebinding.	
		
		
	Clusterrole = PM
	Namespacerole = CM
	
	Cluster = country = Clusterrole/Clusterrole binding
	Namespace = state = Namespace/Clusterrole
	
	
